    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA81-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu viṉaimuṟṟiya talaivaṉ pākaṟku uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE who had finished [his] work said to the charioteer.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA81">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            irunilaṅ kuṟaiyak koṭṭip parintiṉ</l>
<l>            ṟāti pōkiya vacaivi ṉōṉṟāṇ</l>
<l>            maṉṉar matikku māṇviṉaip puravi</l>
<l>            koymmayi reruttiṟ peymmaṇi yārppap</l>
<l>            pūṇkatil pākaniṉ ṟērē pūṇṭā </l>
<l>            ḻāka vaṉamulaik karaivalan teṟippa</l>
<l>            vaḻutaṉa ḷuṟaiyu mammā varivai</l>
<l>            viruntayar viruppoṭu vantaṉa ḷacaiiya</l>
<l>            muṟuva liṉṉakai kāṇka</l>
<l>            muṟupakai taṇittaṉa ṉuravuvāḻ vēntē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>May the horses of glorious work that the king values,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with untiringly enduring legs that have gone galopping</l>
<l rend="indent2">speedily(?), pounding the dark ground, so that it is worn</l>
<l>    be yoked to your chariot, charioteer,</l>
<l rend="indent">so that the bells they wear on [their] necks with trimmed hair roar.</l>
<l>May we see the smiling sweet smile that became weary of her</l>
<l rend="indent">who came up(?)<note place="foot">Here we have, with <term xml:lang="ta">aḻutaṉaḷ</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">vantaṉaḷ</term> (line 8), two p.a. forms with the <term xml:lang="ta">aṉ</term>-infix, but definitely not in finite function.</note> with longing to engage in [preparing] a feast,</l>
<l rend="indent">the pretty dark young woman who remained crying(?)</l>
<l rend="indent">so that [her] beautiful breast, [her] bosom hung with ornaments, </l>
<l>is heaving, strength wearing away.</l>
<l>The king in whom strength lives has [just] appeased the enmity</l>
<l rend="indent3">he met with.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
        </text>
